name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Pokemon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is the last card in your hand, you may play it onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokemon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't use that attack.

name: Yanma
flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Pineco
flavorText: It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Celebi
flavorText: This Pokemon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: For each of your Benched Pokemon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon and put it onto that Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Seedot
flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokemon.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: A Pokemon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, each Supporter card in your opponent's hand has the effect "Draw 3 cards." (This happens instead of the card's usual effect.)
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Nincada
flavorText: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Ninjask
flavorText: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may search your deck for Shedinja and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokemon and all attached cards and puts them on the bottom of their deck.

name: Genesect
flavorText: This Pokemon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Skiddo
flavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gogoat
flavorText: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Dhelmise
flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Orbeetle V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Orbeetle VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Zarude V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: You may attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, heal all damage from that Pokemon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Discard the other cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Leon card in your discard pile.

name: Flareon
flavorText: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokemon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Grass Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Slugma
flavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Magcargo
flavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Talonflame V
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Discard your hand and draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Fire Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Wailmer
flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Wailord
flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
Ability1Text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon, remove all Special Conditions from it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavorText: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.
Attack2Text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their hand.

name: Samurott
flavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: You may put 2 Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their hand.

name: Galarian Darmanitan V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Darmanitan VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Chewtle
flavorText: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Drednaw
flavorText: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokemon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.
Attack1Text: If you played Nessa from your hand during this turn, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Cramorant
flavorText: Cramorant's gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Arrokuda from your Bench. This attack does 60 damage for each Arrokuda you discarded in this way.

name: Arrokuda
flavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokemon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Arrokuda and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Barraskewda
flavorText: This Pokemon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon for each damage counter on that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Pikachu V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Pikachu VMAX
Attack1Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poke Ball, it has zapped many people.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to your Lightning Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokemon is Knocked Out.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Water Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokemon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon, and this attack does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon V or Pokemon-GX. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Ampharos V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Raikou
flavorText: This rough Pokemon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokemon. It's soaking up static electricity because it can't produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: One alone can emit only trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: These Pokemon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if they attach an Energy card from their hand to the Defending Pokemon, put 6 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokemon and 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zekrom
flavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V or Pokemon-GX, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Pincurchin
flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokemon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if your Active Pokemon has any Psychic Energy attached, you may heal 20 damage from it, and it recovers from a Special Condition.

name: Girafarig
flavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: You may have your opponent shuffle their hand into their deck. If you do, your opponent draws 4 cards.

name: Shedinja
flavorText: A most peculiar Pokemon that somehow appears in a Poke Ball when a Nincada evolves.
Ability1Text: Put this Pokemon into play only with the effect of Ninjask's Cast-Off Shell Ability. (When you are setting up to play, you cannot put it face down as your Active Pokemon or on your Bench.)
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon until its remaining HP is 10.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: There's a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Banette
flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may devolve 1 of your opponent's Benched evolved Pokemon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.

name: Duskull
flavorText: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it's said.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokemon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.
Ability1Text: All Special Energy attached to Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's) provide Colorless Energy and have no other effect.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon and a Supporter card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Woobat
flavorText: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it's evidence that Woobat live there.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If you have any cards in your hand, this attack does nothing.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won't be able to fly for a little while.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to this Pokemon.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokemon Tools from your Pokemon. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Xerneas
flavorText: When the horns on its head shine in seven different colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
Attack1Text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Diancie
flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, any damage done to your Pokemon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Milcery
flavorText: This Pokemon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may have each player draw a card.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Zacian
flavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokemon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has any Pokemon VMAX in play, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Wooper
flavorText: This Pokemon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
flavorText: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.
Attack2Text: If you have exactly 2, 4, or 6 Prize cards remaining, this attack does nothing.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Phanpy
flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Donphan
flavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Hitmontop
flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: If you played Bea from your hand during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Regirock
flavorText: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Born when all of Zygarde's cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.

name: Mudbray
flavorText: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokemon. It's skilled at making use of mud.

name: Mudsdale
flavorText: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokemon to scrap a truck with a single kick.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Coalossal V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Coalossal VMAX
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is an Energy card, this attack does 90 more damage, and attach that card to this Pokemon.

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct
flavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokemon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon used Full Nelson during your last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Zamazenta
flavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Pokemon VMAX.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks do 50 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sableye
flavorText: This Pokemon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't use that attack.

name: Drapion V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Sandile
flavorText: Sandile's still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It's called "the cleaner of the desert."
Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokemon living in your room.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: This Pokemon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokemon Tool card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those cards into your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Galarian Meowth
flavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokemon's body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Galarian Perrserker
flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokemon lives for the thrill of battle.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If any of them are heads, your opponent reveals their hand. Then, for each heads, discard a Trainer card from your opponent's hand.

name: Forretress
flavorText: In the moment that it gulps down its prey, the inside of its shell is exposed, but to this day, no one has ever seen that sight.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: Both Active Pokemon are Knocked Out.

name: Steelix V
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Beldum
flavorText: If you anger it, it will do more than rampage. It will also burst out strong magnetism, causing nearby machines to break.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Metang
flavorText: It flies at high speeds around the skies. When it finds its prey, Metang takes a firm grip with its sharp claws and never lets go.

name: Metagross
flavorText: It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.
Ability1Text: Your Pokemon in play have no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Jirachi
flavorText: Once every 1,000 years, the singing of a pure voice will rouse this Pokemon from its near-perpetual slumber. It wakes for only seven days.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card back on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 7 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Lucario
flavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Dialga
flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Metal Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Excadrill
flavorText: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn't very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: This Pokemon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Galarian Stunfisk
flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.

name: Aegislash V

name: Aegislash VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card you have taken.

name: Magearna
flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Duraludon
flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 5 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does nothing.

name: Taillow
flavorText: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Swellow
flavorText: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.
Attack2Text: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Whismur
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Loudred
flavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokemon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Exploud
flavorText: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor—or like an earthquake has struck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokemon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Rayquaza
flavorText: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.
Attack1Text: Discard all basic Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 damage for each type of basic Energy you discarded in this way.

name: Chatot
flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Togekiss V

name: Togekiss VMAX
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tornadus

Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Pikipek
flavorText: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!

name: Trumbeak
flavorText: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

name: Toucannon
flavorText: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokemon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.

Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

name: Coalossal V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Galarian Obstagoon

flavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokemon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
